The paper deals with dynamic data structures for maintaining hierarchical clustering, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and clustering (cs.DM). The use of k-center clustering and diameter k-clustering suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. Finally, the use of approximation algorithms and probabilistic analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
